metadata.name: Theion Manteia #1/5
metadata.description:
In ancient Greek mythology, Mount Olympus was where the gods lived. While living on Mount Olympus, the gods were able to monitor world events and people's lives.

According to some myths, the gods descended to earth to interact with humans and intervene in their lives. But in general, the gods observed people's lives and watched their actions and decisions.
